# Windows PowerShell Shell

This project runs on **Windows PowerShell 5.x**. `&&` is **not** a valid statement separator and will fail with a parser error.

## Do

- Set the Shell tool `working_directory` to the project path instead of `cd ... && <command>`.
- Chain commands with `;` only when both must run in one invocation.
- Run quality checks as standalone commands from the repo root:

```powershell
pnpm exec tsc --noEmit
pnpm lint
```

## Don't

```powershell
# BAD — && fails in PowerShell 5.x
cd "c:\development\eagle-motors\eagle-ford" && pnpm exec tsc --noEmit

# BAD — unnecessary truncation
pnpm exec tsc --noEmit 2>&1 | Select-Object -First 30
```

## Examples

```powershell
# GOOD — use working_directory: c:\development\eagle-motors\eagle-ford
pnpm exec tsc --noEmit

# GOOD — if chaining is required
Set-Location "c:\development\eagle-motors\eagle-ford"; pnpm lint
```
